\c 28
\s1 The daily offerings
\p
\v 1 TUHAN berbicara kepada Musa,
\v 2 “Perintahkanlah dan sampaikanlah kepada orang Israel, supaya mereka memperhatikan waktu-waktu yang sudah ditentukan untuk memberikan persembahan kepada-Ku, berupa persembahan makanan dan kurban bakaran yang baunya menyenangkan bagi-Ku.
\v 3 Katakan kepada mereka inilah kurban bakaran yang harus dipersembahkan kepada TUHAN setiap hari, yaitu dua ekor anak domba jantan yang berumur satu tahun dan tidak ada cacatnya;
\v 4 yang seekor harus dipersembahkan pada pagi hari dan yang seekor lagi dipersembahkan pada waktu [matahari terbenam//sore].
\v 5 Bersama dengan itu, harus memberikan persembahan kurban sajian, yaitu sepersepuluh efa tepung terbaik diolah dengan seperempat hin minyak zaitun murni.
\v 6 Itu merupakan kurban bakaran tetap yang pertama kali dipersembahkan di gunung Sinai, kurban bakaran yang baunya menyenangkan bagi TUHAN.
\v 7 Setiap mempersembahkan anak domba, harus juga mempersembahkan seperempat hin air anggur bagi TUHAN yang disiramkan di tempat kudus.
\v 8 Hal yang sama juga dilakukan ketika mempersembahkan anak domba pada waktu [matahari terbenam//sore], harus disertai dengan air anggur. Bau kurban bakaran itu itu menyenangkan bagi TUHAN.”
\s1 Persembahan pada hari Sabat
\p
\v 9 Persembahan pada hari Sabat, “Dua ekor domba yang berumur setahun dan tidak bercacat, dua persepuluh efa tepung diolah dengan minyak zaitun sebagai kurban sajian, dan persembahan air anggur.
\v 10 Itulah persembahan bakaran setiap hari Sabat, selain kurban bakaran setiap hari dan persembahan air anggur.”
\s1 Persembahan setiap bulan
\p
\v 11 Pada permulaan setiap bulan kamu harus mempersembahkan kurban bakaran kepada TUHAN, “Dua ekor lembu jantan muda, seekor domba jantan dan tujuh ekor anak domba jantan berumur setahun, masing-masing tidak ada cacatnya.\ v 12 Also bring with each bull an offering of six quarts/liters of nice flour mixed with\add olive\add* oil. With each male sheep make an offering of four quarts of nice flour mixed with\add olive\add* oil.
\v 13 Also bring an offering of two quarts/liters of nice flour mixed with\add olive\add* oil with each lamb. When all of these are burned\add on the altar\add*, the smell will be very pleasing to me.
\v 14 With each bull, also bring two quarts/liters of wine. With each male sheep, bring ◄1-1/3 quarts/1.2 liters► of wine. With each lamb, bring one quart/liter of wine. These offerings must be brought on the first day of each month and burned completely\add on the altar\add*.
\v 15 In addition to these offerings that you burn, you must bring to me one goat for an offering\add to enable me to forgive you for the sins you have committed\add*.”
\s1 The sacrifices during the Festivals of Passover and Unleavened Bread
\p
\v 16 “The Passover Festival must be celebrated to \add honor\add* me\add each year\add* on the fourteenth day of the first month \add of eachyear\add*.
\v 17 The Festival of Unleavened Bread will start on the next day. For the following seven days, the bread that you eat must be made without yeast.
\v 18 On the first day of that festival, you must gather together to worship me, and you must not do any work.
\v 19 On that day, you must bring to me for an offering that will be completely burned\add on the altar\add* two young bulls, one male sheep, and seven male lambs that are one year-old. They must all have no defects.
\v 20 With each of these bulls, bring a grain offering of grain, consisting of six quarts/liters of nice flour mixed with\add olive\add* oil. With the male sheep, bring an offering of grain consisting of four quarts/liters of nice flour mixed with\add olive\add* oil.
\v 21 With each of the seven lambs, bring an offering of two quarts/liters of nice flour mixed with\add olive\add* oil.
\v 22 Also bring one goat for a sacrifice to cause you to be forgiven for your sin.
\v 23 Bring these offerings in addition to the offerings that you bring each morning.
\v 24 The smell of the grain that is burned \add on the altar\add* each day for seven days will be very pleasing to me. Bringthe grain in addition to the animals and the wine that you burn \add on thealtar\add*.
\v 25 On the seventh day of that festival, you must \add again\add* gather together to worship me, and you must not do any work.”
\s1 The sacrifices during the Harvest Festival
\p
\v 26 “On the day of the Harvest Festival, when you bring to me the first grain that you have harvested, you must gather together to worship me. Do not do any work on that day.
\v 27 Bring to me two young bulls, one male sheep, and seven male lambs that are one year-old. When they are completely burned\add on the altar\add*, the smell will be very pleasing to me.
\v 28 Also bring a grain offering of nice flour mixed with \add olive\add* oil. For each bull, bring six quarts/liters, and with each male sheep, bring four quarts/liters,
\v 29 and with each of the lambs bring two quarts/liters.
\v 30 Also sacrifice one male goat to cause you to be forgiven for your sins.
\v 31 Bring these offerings and the offering of wine in addition to the animals and grain that you burn\add on the altar\add* each day. \add And remember that\add* the animals that you sacrifice must have no defects.”